6.1:
Come — let us return to Yahweh.
He has torn us, yes, but he will heal us;
he has struck us down, but he will bind up our wounds.

6.2:
After two days he will give us life again;
on the third day he will raise us up —
and we will live in his presence.

6.10:
I have seen a horrifying thing in Israel's house:
Ephraim has gone over entirely to prostitution;
Israel is unclean.

14.6:
His new branches will spread wide;
he will carry the beauty of the olive —
and the whole air around him will carry the fragrance of Lebanon's forests.

11.2:
The more I called, the further they walked away.
They offered sacrifice after sacrifice to the Baals;
they burned incense to carved images.

11.10:
They will follow Yahweh;
he will roar like a lion — and when he roars,
his children will come running, trembling, from the west.
